& [ExplicitEulerBridgeRestraintSynthesis] is a project-local finite synthesis contract
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is dc514f6c-3433-408b-bc05-3a266a9d2a38
  + [manifest_uuid] is 775f7413-dd92-4f1e-ba29-56b02a20d523
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is 51d664ba-6608-46b3-9f34-e2cadfc13aaf
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is synthesize recent explicit/Euler bridge records and decide whether kernel refinement should pause
  + [not_purpose] is new numerical implementation, proof, disproof, RH evidence, zero certification, critical-line authority, or explicit/Euler identity fusion

  = must: inspect the bridge chain from explicit/Euler cutoff comparison through bias-tuned kernel atlas
  = must: preserve explicit-formula x-domain residuals, Euler/log-derivative Re(s)>1 cutoffs, exact finite Lambda cutoff residuals, and explicit projected Lambda residuals as separate identities
  = must: evaluate whether the latest kernel work produced a dominant correction or only a Pareto tradeoff
  = must: keep special-prime observations subordinate to whole-field objects
  = must: name the next useful direction only after restraint is decided
  = must: mark proof_status as finite_restraint_synthesis_not_rh_evidence
  - never: reopen kernel refinement without new source-defined purpose
  - never: infer RH proof, disproof, zero certification, or critical-line truth from finite synthesis

& [BridgeRecordsToSynthesize] is the bounded source set
  + [explicit_euler_cutoff_bridge] is complementary rails, no scalar identity
  + [scale_law_comparison] is coordinate-law diagnosis, no universal law or bridge identity
  + [lambda_mellin_bridge] is coherent shared weighted Lambda unit, explicit projection residual plateau near 0.202
  + [partial_summation_bridge] is exact audit identity for exact psi and no reduction for sampled psi_hat
  + [cesaro_mellin_bridge] is bridge residual improvement with smoothing bias increase
  + [bias_tuned_kernel_bridge] is alpha Pareto dial with no dominating alpha

& [BridgeRestraintSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and synthesis_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_bounded_bridge_restraint_synthesis_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is the branch has produced enough coherent boundary information to decide whether more kernels are purpose-relevant

(explicit_euler_bridge_restraint_synthesis) :finite bridge branch restraint: /synthesize, decide pause, return whole-field/ |proof authority|
  + [inside] is bounded synthesis of prior finite bridge diagnostics
  + [boundary] is branch-direction decision only
  |outside| RH proof, disproof, zero certification, global explicit/Euler identity, critical-line evidence, and new unsourced implementation
